{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17629526","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17629526"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:07:14+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:07:14+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17286"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17286","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17286"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0,0,0.56,0.33]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9976"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76961"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9976","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9976"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17286"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62466"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23369"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23373"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76961","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76961"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EYour study group is revising the upper limb myotomes.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following reflexes is associated with myotomes C7 and C8?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Biceps","Quadriceps","Achilles","Triceps","Brachioradialis"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Etriceps\u003C/strong\u003E reflex is associated with the C7 and C8 myotomes. This reflex involves the extension of the elbow joint when the triceps tendon is tapped.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ebiceps\u003C/strong\u003E reflex is associated with the C5 and C6 myotomes, involving flexion of the elbow joint when the biceps tendon is tapped.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Equadriceps\u003C/strong\u003E reflex, also known as the patellar reflex, is associated with the L3 and L4 myotomes, with extension of the knee joint when the patellar tendon is tapped.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003EAchilles\u003C/strong\u003E reflex is associated with the S1 and S2 myotomes, with plantar flexion of the foot when the Achilles tendon is tapped.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ebrachioradialis\u003C/strong\u003E reflex is associated with the C5 and C6 myotomes, involving flexion and supination of the forearm when the brachioradialis tendon is tapped.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The triceps reflex is associated with the C7 and C8 myotomes.","Understanding the relationship between reflexes and myotomes is crucial for neurological assessment."],"references":["Sonoo M. Recent advances in neuroanatomy: the myotome update. J Neurol Neurosurg Psychiatry. 2023 Aug;94(8):643-648. doi: 10.1136/jnnp-2022-329696. Epub 2023 Jan 18. PMID: 36653172","Kaiser JT, Lugo-Pico JG. Neuroanatomy, Spinal Nerves. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK542218/","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Science","Howard, R., Kullmann, D., Werring, D., \u0026 Zandi, M. (Eds.). (2024). Neurology: a queen square textbook. John Wiley \u0026 Sons"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type